.Dd June 2, 2026
.Dt SF 1
.Os
.Sh NAME
.Nm sf
.Nd filter music files by Matroska tags
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.Nm
.Op Ar expression ...
.Sh DESCRIPTION
.Nm
expands music files to song references and writes matching references to
standard output.
If standard input is not a terminal, input lines are read as paths or song
references.
Otherwise,
.Nm
scans regular files in
.Ev XDG_MUSIC_DIR ,
the XDG user music directory, or
.Pa ~/Music .
.Pp
A song reference has the form
.Ar path Ns # Ns Ar chapter-id .
When an input line is only a path,
.Nm
expands all chapters in that file.
.Sh EXPRESSIONS
An expression is made from predicates:
.Bd -literal -offset indent
field operator value
.Ed
.Pp
Fields are
.Cm date ,
.Cm orig-date ,
.Cm artist ,
.Cm title ,
.Cm genre ,
.Cm album ,
.Cm track ,
and
.Cm disc .
Operators are
.Cm = ,
.Cm != ,
.Cm < ,
.Cm <= ,
.Cm > ,
.Cm >= ,
and
.Cm ~ .
The
.Cm ~
operator matches an extended regular expression and is valid only for text
fields.
.Pp
Predicates may be combined with
.Cm and ,
.Cm or ,
.Cm not ,
and parentheses.
.Sh SEE ALSO
.Xr sp 1 ,
.Xr sq 1
